STEP-1

Transform the ticket detail page into a real-time incident command center.

---

## Layout

Split into 3 sections:

LEFT:
- Ticket details
- Description
- Attachments

CENTER:
- Activity timeline (live updates)
- Chat / comments

RIGHT:
- SLA timer (countdown)
- Assigned engineer
- Priority + status
- Action buttons

---

## SLA Timer

- Live countdown
- Color logic:
  Green → >50% time
  Yellow → <50%
  Red → overdue

---

## Activity Timeline

- Show all actions:
  created, assigned, updated, closed
- Include user + timestamp

---

## Real-time updates

Use:
- WebSocket or polling

---

## Chat System

- Internal comments
- Mention users (@Nigam)
- Attach files

---

## Action Buttons

- Assign engineer
- Escalate
- Change priority
- Close ticket

---

## UI

- Card-based layout
- Smooth transitions
- Highlight active activity

---

## Deliver

- Ticket detail UI
- Real-time updates
- Activity timeline system

STEP-2

Build an SLA monitoring and alert system.

---

## Logic

If remaining time:

< 50% → warning  
< 20% → high alert  
< 0 → breach  

---

## Actions

- Notify engineer
- Notify manager
- Highlight ticket in dashboard

---

## UI

- Show badge:
  "At Risk"
  "Breaching Soon"

---

## Optional

Auto escalate to manager

STEP-3

Implement smart ticket assignment based on engineer workload.

---

## Logic

- Count active tickets per engineer
- Consider priority weight:
  High = 3
  Medium = 2
  Low = 1

---

## Assign to:

Engineer with lowest total load

